{
  "texts": [
    "As for adjacency-matrix encodings, they often incur sizable losses-we hypothesize this is due to these representations being \"misaligned\" with counting tasks and inflating the description length to O(n 2) with potentially distracting tokens.We now probe robustness w.r.t.",
    "the inherent symmetries of the edge-list and adjacency-list encodings.",
    "In fig. 3b, we report accuracy difference obtained by a (partly) shuffled structure as opposed to its canonicalized form.",
    "The fine-tuned G1 models are again, to be the most brittle on average, with the largest drops on edge-list.",
    "In sorted edge-list, the edges are grouped by source node, so each node's neighbors appear contiguously."
  ]
}